{
  "video_id": "C44r6knuJtU",
  "title": "Why genetic research must be more diverse | Keolu Fox",
  "es": 0,
  "json": [
    {
      "index": 1,
      "start_time": 12866.0,
      "end_time": 14710.0,
      "text": "As a little Hawaiian,"
    },
    {
      "index": 2,
      "start_time": 14950.0,
      "end_time": 17477.0,
      "text": "my mom and auntie always told me stories about Kalaupapa --"
    },
    {
      "index": 3,
      "start_time": 17501.0,
      "end_time": 18822.0,
      "text": "the Hawaiian leper colony"
    },
    {
      "index": 4,
      "start_time": 18846.0,
      "end_time": 21673.0,
      "text": "surrounded by the highest sea cliffs in the world --"
    },
    {
      "index": 5,
      "start_time": 21697.0,
      "end_time": 23109.0,
      "text": "and Father Damien,"
    },
    {
      "index": 6,
      "start_time": 23133.0,
      "end_time": 26561.0,
      "text": "the Belgian missionary who gave his life for the Hawaiian community."
    },
    {
      "index": 7,
      "start_time": 27102.0,
      "end_time": 28465.0,
      "text": "As a young nurse,"
    },
    {
      "index": 8,
      "start_time": 28489.0,
      "end_time": 31430.0,
      "text": "my aunt trained the nuns caring for the remaining lepers"
    },
    {
      "index": 9,
      "start_time": 31454.0,
      "end_time": 34731.0,
      "text": "almost a 100 years after Father Damien died of leprosy."
    },
    {
      "index": 10,
      "start_time": 36501.0,
      "end_time": 38172.0,
      "text": "I remember stories she told"
    },
    {
      "index": 11,
      "start_time": 38196.0,
      "end_time": 41147.0,
      "text": "about traveling down switchback cliff paths on a mule,"
    },
    {
      "index": 12,
      "start_time": 41172.0,
      "end_time": 44303.0,
      "text": "while my uncle played her favorite hula songs on the ukulele"
    },
    {
      "index": 13,
      "start_time": 44327.0,
      "end_time": 46400.0,
      "text": "all the way down to Kalaupapa."
    },
    {
      "index": 14,
      "start_time": 46730.0,
      "end_time": 48230.0,
      "text": "You see, as a youngster,"
    },
    {
      "index": 15,
      "start_time": 48255.0,
      "end_time": 50191.0,
      "text": "I was always curious about a few things."
    },
    {
      "index": 16,
      "start_time": 50681.0,
      "end_time": 55730.0,
      "text": "First was why a Belgian missionary chose to live in complete isolation"
    },
    {
      "index": 17,
      "start_time": 55755.0,
      "end_time": 56945.0,
      "text": "in Kalaupapa,"
    },
    {
      "index": 18,
      "start_time": 56969.0,
      "end_time": 59199.0,
      "text": "knowing he would inevitably contract leprosy"
    },
    {
      "index": 19,
      "start_time": 59223.0,
      "end_time": 61603.0,
      "text": "from the community of people he sought to help."
    },
    {
      "index": 20,
      "start_time": 62256.0,
      "end_time": 64593.0,
      "text": "And secondly,"
    },
    {
      "index": 21,
      "start_time": 64617.00000000001,
      "end_time": 66978.0,
      "text": "where did the leprosy bacteria come from?"
    },
    {
      "index": 22,
      "start_time": 67200.0,
      "end_time": 68756.0,
      "text": "And why were KƒÅnaka Maoli,"
    },
    {
      "index": 23,
      "start_time": 68781.0,
      "end_time": 71300.0,
      "text": "the indigenous people of Hawaii,"
    },
    {
      "index": 24,
      "start_time": 71540.0,
      "end_time": 75416.0,
      "text": "so susceptible to developing leprosy, or \"mai Pake?\""
    },
    {
      "index": 25,
      "start_time": 75853.0,
      "end_time": 79583.0,
      "text": "This got my curious about what makes us unique as Hawaiians --"
    },
    {
      "index": 26,
      "start_time": 79607.0,
      "end_time": 81448.0,
      "text": "namely, our genetic makeup."
    },
    {
      "index": 27,
      "start_time": 82964.0,
      "end_time": 84908.0,
      "text": "But it wasn&#39;t until high school,"
    },
    {
      "index": 28,
      "start_time": 84932.0,
      "end_time": 86544.0,
      "text": "through the Human Genome Project,"
    },
    {
      "index": 29,
      "start_time": 86568.0,
      "end_time": 88767.0,
      "text": "that I realized I wasn&#39;t alone"
    },
    {
      "index": 30,
      "start_time": 88791.0,
      "end_time": 91619.0,
      "text": "in trying to connect our unique genetic ancestry"
    },
    {
      "index": 31,
      "start_time": 91643.0,
      "end_time": 95325.0,
      "text": "to our potential health, wellness and illness."
    },
    {
      "index": 32,
      "start_time": 96610.0,
      "end_time": 97211.0,
      "text": "You see,"
    },
    {
      "index": 33,
      "start_time": 97235.0,
      "end_time": 99340.0,
      "text": "the 2.7 billion-dollar project"
    },
    {
      "index": 34,
      "start_time": 99580.0,
      "end_time": 103480.0,
      "text": "promised an era of predictive and preventative medicine"
    },
    {
      "index": 35,
      "start_time": 103720.0,
      "end_time": 105485.0,
      "text": "based on our unique genetic makeup."
    },
    {
      "index": 36,
      "start_time": 105849.0,
      "end_time": 107525.0,
      "text": "So to me it always seemed obvious"
    },
    {
      "index": 37,
      "start_time": 107549.0,
      "end_time": 110277.0,
      "text": "that in order to achieve this dream,"
    },
    {
      "index": 38,
      "start_time": 110301.0,
      "end_time": 114314.0,
      "text": "we would need to sequence a diverse cohort of people"
    },
    {
      "index": 39,
      "start_time": 114338.0,
      "end_time": 117741.0,
      "text": "to obtain the full spectrum of human genetic variation on the planet."
    },
    {
      "index": 40,
      "start_time": 118303.0,
      "end_time": 120875.0,
      "text": "That&#39;s why 10 years later,"
    },
    {
      "index": 41,
      "start_time": 120899.0,
      "end_time": 122573.0,
      "text": "it continues to shock me,"
    },
    {
      "index": 42,
      "start_time": 122597.0,
      "end_time": 125811.0,
      "text": "knowing that 96 percent of genome studies"
    },
    {
      "index": 43,
      "start_time": 125835.0,
      "end_time": 129414.0,
      "text": "associating common genetic variation with specific diseases"
    },
    {
      "index": 44,
      "start_time": 129439.0,
      "end_time": 133239.0,
      "text": "have focused exclusively on individuals of European ancestry."
    },
    {
      "index": 45,
      "start_time": 134690.0,
      "end_time": 135477.0,
      "text": "Now you don&#39;t need a PhD"
    },
    {
      "index": 46,
      "start_time": 135502.0,
      "end_time": 138535.0,
      "text": "to see that that leaves four percent for the rest of diversity."
    },
    {
      "index": 47,
      "start_time": 139164.0,
      "end_time": 141291.0,
      "text": "And in my own searching,"
    },
    {
      "index": 48,
      "start_time": 141316.0,
      "end_time": 143825.0,
      "text": "I&#39;ve discovered that far less than one percent"
    },
    {
      "index": 49,
      "start_time": 143849.0,
      "end_time": 146923.0,
      "text": "have actually focused on indigenous communities, like myself."
    },
    {
      "index": 50,
      "start_time": 147481.0,
      "end_time": 149528.0,
      "text": "So that begs the question:"
    },
    {
      "index": 51,
      "start_time": 149552.0,
      "end_time": 152990.0,
      "text": "Who is the Human Genome Project actually for?"
    },
    {
      "index": 52,
      "start_time": 152853.0,
      "end_time": 155211.0,
      "text": "Just like we have different colored eyes and hair,"
    },
    {
      "index": 53,
      "start_time": 155235.0,
      "end_time": 156743.0,
      "text": "we metabolize drugs differently"
    },
    {
      "index": 54,
      "start_time": 156767.0,
      "end_time": 158634.0,
      "text": "based on the variation in our genomes."
    },
    {
      "index": 55,
      "start_time": 158978.0,
      "end_time": 162415.0,
      "text": "So how many of you would be shocked to learn"
    },
    {
      "index": 56,
      "start_time": 162439.0,
      "end_time": 165221.0,
      "text": "that 95 percent of clinical trials"
    },
    {
      "index": 57,
      "start_time": 165245.0,
      "end_time": 169661.0,
      "text": "have also exclusively featured individuals of European ancestry?"
    },
    {
      "index": 58,
      "start_time": 170387.0,
      "end_time": 171722.0,
      "text": "This bias"
    },
    {
      "index": 59,
      "start_time": 171746.0,
      "end_time": 175587.0,
      "text": "and systematic lack of engagement of indigenous people"
    },
    {
      "index": 60,
      "start_time": 175611.0,
      "end_time": 178595.0,
      "text": "in both clinical trials and genome studies"
    },
    {
      "index": 61,
      "start_time": 178619.0,
      "end_time": 181559.0,
      "text": "is partially the result of a history of distrust."
    },
    {
      "index": 62,
      "start_time": 182893.0,
      "end_time": 184430.0,
      "text": "For example,"
    },
    {
      "index": 63,
      "start_time": 184670.0,
      "end_time": 187996.0,
      "text": "in 1989, researchers from Arizona State University"
    },
    {
      "index": 64,
      "start_time": 188200.0,
      "end_time": 191586.0,
      "text": "obtained blood samples from Arizona&#39;s Havasupai tribe,"
    },
    {
      "index": 65,
      "start_time": 191610.0,
      "end_time": 194544.0,
      "text": "promising to alleviate the burden of type 2 diabetes"
    },
    {
      "index": 66,
      "start_time": 194568.0,
      "end_time": 196428.0,
      "text": "that was plaguing their community,"
    },
    {
      "index": 67,
      "start_time": 196452.0,
      "end_time": 200337.0,
      "text": "only to turn around and use those exact same samples --"
    },
    {
      "index": 68,
      "start_time": 200361.0,
      "end_time": 202640.0,
      "text": "without the Havasupai&#39;s consent --"
    },
    {
      "index": 69,
      "start_time": 202880.0,
      "end_time": 205593.0,
      "text": "to study rates of schizophrenia, inbreeding,"
    },
    {
      "index": 70,
      "start_time": 205617.0,
      "end_time": 208591.0,
      "text": "and challenge the Havasupai&#39;s origin story."
    },
    {
      "index": 71,
      "start_time": 209319.0,
      "end_time": 211861.0,
      "text": "When the Havasupai found out,"
    },
    {
      "index": 72,
      "start_time": 211885.0,
      "end_time": 215780.0,
      "text": "they sued successfully for $700,000,"
    },
    {
      "index": 73,
      "start_time": 215102.0,
      "end_time": 220445.0,
      "text": "and they banned ASU from conducting research on their reservation."
    },
    {
      "index": 74,
      "start_time": 220961.0,
      "end_time": 224215.0,
      "text": "This culminated in a sort of domino effect"
    },
    {
      "index": 75,
      "start_time": 224239.0,
      "end_time": 226100.0,
      "text": "with local tribes in the Southwest --"
    },
    {
      "index": 76,
      "start_time": 226250.0,
      "end_time": 227454.0,
      "text": "including the Navajo Nation,"
    },
    {
      "index": 77,
      "start_time": 227478.0,
      "end_time": 229565.0,
      "text": "one of the largest tribes in the country --"
    },
    {
      "index": 78,
      "start_time": 229589.0,
      "end_time": 231836.0,
      "text": "putting a moratorium on genetic research."
    },
    {
      "index": 79,
      "start_time": 231860.0,
      "end_time": 234741.0,
      "text": "Now despite this history of distrust,"
    },
    {
      "index": 80,
      "start_time": 234765.0,
      "end_time": 239239.0,
      "text": "I still believe that indigenous people can benefit from genetic research."
    },
    {
      "index": 81,
      "start_time": 239264.0,
      "end_time": 241509.0,
      "text": "And if we don&#39;t do something soon,"
    },
    {
      "index": 82,
      "start_time": 241533.0,
      "end_time": 244399.0,
      "text": "the gap in health disparities is going to continue to widen."
    },
    {
      "index": 83,
      "start_time": 245113.0,
      "end_time": 246518.0,
      "text": "Hawaii, for example,"
    },
    {
      "index": 84,
      "start_time": 246542.0,
      "end_time": 250249.0,
      "text": "has the longest life expectancy on average of any state in the US,"
    },
    {
      "index": 85,
      "start_time": 250273.0,
      "end_time": 253130.0,
      "text": "yet native Hawaiians like myself"
    },
    {
      "index": 86,
      "start_time": 253154.0,
      "end_time": 256240.0,
      "text": "die a full decade before our non-native counterparts,"
    },
    {
      "index": 87,
      "start_time": 256264.0,
      "end_time": 260315.0,
      "text": "because we have some of the highest rates of type 2 diabetes,"
    },
    {
      "index": 88,
      "start_time": 260339.0,
      "end_time": 261490.0,
      "text": "obesity,"
    },
    {
      "index": 89,
      "start_time": 261514.0,
      "end_time": 264390.0,
      "text": "and the number one and number two killers in the US:"
    },
    {
      "index": 90,
      "start_time": 264630.0,
      "end_time": 265902.0,
      "text": "cardiovascular disease and cancer."
    },
    {
      "index": 91,
      "start_time": 265926.0,
      "end_time": 267645.0,
      "text": "So how do we ensure"
    },
    {
      "index": 92,
      "start_time": 267669.0,
      "end_time": 270820.0,
      "text": "the populations of people that need genome sequencing the most"
    },
    {
      "index": 93,
      "start_time": 270844.0,
      "end_time": 272264.0,
      "text": "are not the last to benefit?"
    },
    {
      "index": 94,
      "start_time": 272671.0,
      "end_time": 277394.0,
      "text": "My vision is to make genetic research more native,"
    },
    {
      "index": 95,
      "start_time": 277418.0,
      "end_time": 279829.0,
      "text": "to indigenize genome sequencing technology."
    },
    {
      "index": 96,
      "start_time": 280902.0,
      "end_time": 283933.0,
      "text": "Traditionally, genomes are sequenced in laboratories."
    },
    {
      "index": 97,
      "start_time": 284555.0,
      "end_time": 287143.0,
      "text": "Here&#39;s an image of your classic genome sequencer."
    },
    {
      "index": 98,
      "start_time": 287167.0,
      "end_time": 288318.0,
      "text": "It&#39;s huge."
    },
    {
      "index": 99,
      "start_time": 288342.0,
      "end_time": 290940.0,
      "text": "It&#39;s the size of a refrigerator."
    },
    {
      "index": 100,
      "start_time": 290750.0,
      "end_time": 292817.0,
      "text": "There&#39;s this obvious physical limitation."
    },
    {
      "index": 101,
      "start_time": 293321.0,
      "end_time": 296440.0,
      "text": "But what if you could sequence genomes on the fly?"
    },
    {
      "index": 102,
      "start_time": 297210.0,
      "end_time": 300510.0,
      "text": "What if you could fit a genome sequencer in your pocket?"
    },
    {
      "index": 103,
      "start_time": 303848.0,
      "end_time": 306246.0,
      "text": "This nanopore-based sequencer"
    },
    {
      "index": 104,
      "start_time": 306270.0,
      "end_time": 310755.0,
      "text": "is one 10,000th the size of your traditional genome sequencer."
    },
    {
      "index": 105,
      "start_time": 310779.0,
      "end_time": 313000.0,
      "text": "It doesn&#39;t have the same physical limitations,"
    },
    {
      "index": 106,
      "start_time": 313240.0,
      "end_time": 317300.0,
      "text": "in that it&#39;s not tethered to a lab bench with extraneous cords,"
    },
    {
      "index": 107,
      "start_time": 317324.0,
      "end_time": 319849.0,
      "text": "large vats of chemicals or computer monitors."
    },
    {
      "index": 108,
      "start_time": 320456.0,
      "end_time": 325607.0,
      "text": "It allows us to de-black box genome sequencing technology development"
    },
    {
      "index": 109,
      "start_time": 325631.0,
      "end_time": 328243.0,
      "text": "in a way that&#39;s immersive and collaborative,"
    },
    {
      "index": 110,
      "start_time": 328267.0,
      "end_time": 331500.0,
      "text": "activating and empowering indigenous communities ..."
    },
    {
      "index": 111,
      "start_time": 332476.0,
      "end_time": 333917.0,
      "text": "as citizen scientists."
    },
    {
      "index": 112,
      "start_time": 335920.0,
      "end_time": 337647.0,
      "text": "100 years later in Kalaupapa,"
    },
    {
      "index": 113,
      "start_time": 337672.0,
      "end_time": 341911.0,
      "text": "we now have the technology to sequence leprosy bacteria in real time,"
    },
    {
      "index": 114,
      "start_time": 341935.0,
      "end_time": 344823.0,
      "text": "using mobile genome sequencers,"
    },
    {
      "index": 115,
      "start_time": 344847.0,
      "end_time": 347856.0,
      "text": "remote access to the Internet"
    },
    {
      "index": 116,
      "start_time": 347880.0,
      "end_time": 349292.0,
      "text": "and cloud computation."
    },
    {
      "index": 117,
      "start_time": 350440.0,
      "end_time": 353280.0,
      "text": "But only if that&#39;s what Hawaiian people want."
    },
    {
      "index": 118,
      "start_time": 354740.0,
      "end_time": 355370.0,
      "text": "In our space,"
    },
    {
      "index": 119,
      "start_time": 355394.0,
      "end_time": 356844.0,
      "text": "on our terms."
    },
    {
      "index": 120,
      "start_time": 358367.0,
      "end_time": 364172.0,
      "text": "IndiGenomics is about science for the people by the people."
    },
    {
      "index": 121,
      "start_time": 364196.0,
      "end_time": 368141.0,
      "text": "We&#39;ll be starting with a tribal consultation resource,"
    },
    {
      "index": 122,
      "start_time": 368165.0,
      "end_time": 371376.0,
      "text": "focused on educating indigenous communities"
    },
    {
      "index": 123,
      "start_time": 371400.0,
      "end_time": 374419.0,
      "text": "on the potential use and misuse of genetic information."
    },
    {
      "index": 124,
      "start_time": 374861.0,
      "end_time": 378171.0,
      "text": "Eventually we&#39;d like to have our own IndiGenomics research institute"
    },
    {
      "index": 125,
      "start_time": 378195.0,
      "end_time": 379623.0,
      "text": "to conduct our own experiments"
    },
    {
      "index": 126,
      "start_time": 379648.0,
      "end_time": 382783.0,
      "text": "and educate the next generation of indigenous scientists."
    },
    {
      "index": 127,
      "start_time": 383523.0,
      "end_time": 385840.0,
      "text": "In the end,"
    },
    {
      "index": 128,
      "start_time": 385108.0,
      "end_time": 389700.0,
      "text": "indigenous people need to be partners in and not subjects of genetic research."
    },
    {
      "index": 129,
      "start_time": 390179.0,
      "end_time": 392131.0,
      "text": "And for those on the outside,"
    },
    {
      "index": 130,
      "start_time": 392156.0,
      "end_time": 393640.0,
      "text": "just as Father Damien did,"
    },
    {
      "index": 131,
      "start_time": 394625.0,
      "end_time": 398983.0,
      "text": "the research community needs to immerse itself in indigenous culture"
    },
    {
      "index": 132,
      "start_time": 399700.0,
      "end_time": 400960.0,
      "text": "or die trying."
    },
    {
      "index": 133,
      "start_time": 400984.0,
      "end_time": 402188.0,
      "text": "Mahalo."
    },
    {
      "index": 134,
      "start_time": 402213.0,
      "end_time": 407213.0,
      "text": "(Applause)"
    }
  ]
}